A collection of ELF injectors/infectors written for educational purposes.

Within the scope of this toolset 'infecting' is the process of the inserting code into an ELF executabile which redirects control to malicious instructions.

'Injection' is the process of inserting and smuggling a malicious payload into an ELF executable without breaking the executable's integrity.

Infection Techniques:
o  .ctors
o  .dtors
o  entrypoint
o  got poisoning
o  .plt redirection
o  arbitry function hooking

Injection Techniques:
o post-text padding
o pre-text (reverse) padding
o data segment 
